description: Gareth Ainsworth's tenure as Gillingham manager begins with a point on the road at Harrogate.
title: Harrogate Town 1-1 Gillingham: Gareth Ainsworth begins Gills reign with draw
title_page: Harrogate Town 1-1 Gillingham: Gareth Ainsworth begins Gills reign with draw - BBC Sport
maintext:
Harrogate Town have lost just one of their five league games against Gillingham (W3 D1), never conceding more than one goal in any of those matches.
Gillingham have lost eight of their last 10 league games against sides from Yorkshire (W1 D1), though their only victory in that time came in their last meeting with a side form the county â€“ a 1-0 success over Bradford City in March.
Harrogate have won each of their last three home league games and could win four in succession on home soil in the EFL for the first time since March 2021.
